Privacy Policy for YouTube Floater
Effective Date: June 25, 2025

YouTube Floater is a macOS application developed by Jim Brendlinger that allows users to float a YouTube video in a standalone, always-on-top window. This app does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.

Information Collection and Use
The app does not require or collect any user data.

It does not use analytics, third-party SDKs, or tracking mechanisms.

All functionality runs locally on your Mac.

Third-Party Services
YouTube Floater loads publicly available YouTube content, subject to YouTubeâ€™s Terms of Service.

The app itself does not interact with YouTube APIs or collect any data from YouTube.

Security
Because the app does not transmit or store any data, there is minimal security risk. All behavior is confined to your local machine.

Contact
For questions or concerns, contact: jim@sunbirdcomputer.com
